The paper deals with routing problems, which are typically studied in the fields of algorithms and optimization (cs.DS). The use of time windows and the goal of maximizing the number of visited locations or minimizing the number of vehicles suggest a focus on efficiency and resource allocation, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approximation algorithms presented in the paper involve analyzing and optimizing the performance of the algorithm, which is a common theme in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The use of vehicles and routing also suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper deals with optimization problems that involve constraints, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of scientific computing (cs.SI).
